===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|maunde}}, {{m|enm|mande}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|mand}}, {{m|ang|mond||basket}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*mandō||basket}}. Cognate with Dutch {{m|nl|mand}}, {{cog|nds|mande}}, archaic German {{m|de|Mande}}, later influenced by {{etyl|xno|en}} and {{etyl|frm|en}} {{m|frm|mande}} (< {{etyl|gem|en}}). Related to {{l|en|mannequin}}.

